headline: Dover (NYSE:DOV) Projects 2025 Earnings Growth Despite Q1 Revenue Decline
summary: Dover (NYSE:DOV) recently provided new guidance projecting earnings per share for 2025 to fall between $8.04 and $8.24, with anticipated revenue growth of 2% to 4%. Concurrently, the company released its first-quarter results, revealing declines in both sales and net income compared to the previous year, arguably suggesting challenges ahead. Despite this, Dover's stock rose 3% over the past week, aligning with a broader market increase. These factors, combined with the market's 2.3% gain as...

headline: Dover (NYSE:DOV) Misses Q1 Sales Targets
summary: Manufacturing company Dover (NYSE:DOV) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales flat year on year at $1.87 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.05 per share was 3.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
